article.headline: East Tennessee State 56, North Florida 51
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Courtney Pigram scored 12 points to lead East Tennessee State to a 56-51 win over North Florida on Saturday. Pigram offset a cold day from the floor, including 2-of-10 from 3-point range, by converting 6-of-10. Pigram was the only player for East Tennessee State to reach double figures. The Buccaneers (19-8, 13-2) maintained their hold on first place in the Atlantic Sun Conference. After holding a 35-30 lead at halftime, the Bucs stretched the margin to nine points at 51-42 with 3:26 left in the game. North Florida then scored eight of the game's next 10 points to pull within three at 53-50 with 58 seconds remaining. It was as close as the Ospreys got however, as East Tennessee State sank three free throws to secure the win. The Buccaneers converted 12 of their first 13 free throws but managed just 5-of-12 in the final 70 seconds. Neither team shot well from the field with East Tennessee State hitting just 33 percent and North Florida finishing at 34 percent. It was the 13th consecutive loss for North Florida (2-23, 0-14) and extended the team's losing streak against Division 1 opponents to 30 games. James Grimball led North Florida with 15 points while Chris Timberlake added 14.
